# Code Style

## TypeScript / JavaScript

### Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `UserProfile.tsx`)
- Hooks: `use-kebab-case.ts` (e.g., `use-auth.ts`)
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g., `format-date.ts`)
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
- Booleans: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `canEdit` (verb prefix)
- Event handlers: `handleClick`, `handleSubmit` (handle prefix)

### Functions
- Arrow functions for components: `const Component = () => {}`
- Named exports (avoid default exports except pages/layouts)
- Max 20 lines per function (extract if longer)
- Early returns over nested conditionals

### Types
- Explicit return types for public functions
- No `any` (use `unknown` + type guards)
- Interface names: `ComponentNameProps`
- Type definitions co-located or in `types/`

## Python

### Naming (PEP 8)
- Modules: `snake_case.py`
- Classes: `PascalCase`
- Functions: `snake_case`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
- Private: `_leading_underscore`

### Structure
- One class per file (mostly)
- Max 50 lines per function
- Type hints for function signatures
- Docstrings for public APIs (Google style)

## Go

### Naming
- Exported: `PascalCase`
- Unexported: `camelCase`
- Packages: `lowercase` (no underscores)

### Structure
- Interface names: `Reader`, `Writer` (not `IReader`)
- One package per directory
- Return errors as last value
